{"parse":{"title":"Robert Cleghorn","pageid":48289281,"revid":848443817,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Robert_Cleghorn._Photograph_by_Annan._Wellcome_V0028669.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7b/Robert_Cleghorn._Photograph_by_Annan._Wellcome_V0028669.jpg/220px-Robert_Cleghorn._Photograph_by_Annan._Wellcome_V0028669.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"266\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7b/Robert_Cleghorn._Photograph_by_Annan._Wellcome_V0028669.jpg/330px-Robert_Cleghorn._Photograph_by_Annan._Wellcome_V0028669.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7b/Robert_Cleghorn._Photograph_by_Annan._Wellcome_V0028669.jpg/440px-Robert_Cleghorn._Photograph_by_Annan._Wellcome_V0028669.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2512\" data-file-height=\"3034\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Robert_Cleghorn._Photograph_by_Annan._Wellcome_V0028669.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Prof Robert Cleghorn</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Robert Cleghorn</b> <a href=\"/wiki/Fellow_of_the_Royal_Society_of_Edinburgh\" title=\"Fellow of the Royal Society of Edinburgh\">FRSE</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Royal_College_of_Physicians_and_Surgeons_of_Glasgow\" title=\"Royal College of Physicians and Surgeons of Glasgow\">FFPSG</a> PRMS (1755\u20131821) was a Scottish physician and pharmacologist.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Life\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Life</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Family\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Family</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Positions_of_note\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Positions of note</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Life\">Life</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Robert_Cleghorn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Life\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:The_grave_of_Rev_Robert_Cleghorn,_Craigton_Cemetery.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/72/The_grave_of_Rev_Robert_Cleghorn%2C_Craigton_Cemetery.jpg/220px-The_grave_of_Rev_Robert_Cleghorn%2C_Craigton_Cemetery.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"330\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/72/The_grave_of_Rev_Robert_Cleghorn%2C_Craigton_Cemetery.jpg/330px-The_grave_of_Rev_Robert_Cleghorn%2C_Craigton_Cemetery.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/72/The_grave_of_Rev_Robert_Cleghorn%2C_Craigton_Cemetery.jpg/440px-The_grave_of_Rev_Robert_Cleghorn%2C_Craigton_Cemetery.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2056\" data-file-height=\"3088\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:The_grave_of_Rev_Robert_Cleghorn,_Craigton_Cemetery.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The grave of Rev Robert Cleghorn, Craigton Cemetery</div></div></div>\n<p>Little is known of his early life. He is thought to have been born around 1755.<sup id=\"cite_ref-gla_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-gla-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>  He studied medicine at <a href=\"/wiki/Edinburgh_University\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Edinburgh University\">Edinburgh University</a>, graduating MD in 1783. He was in general medical practice as a GP in <a href=\"/wiki/Glasgow\" title=\"Glasgow\">Glasgow</a> from 1785, then in 1788 began lecturing in medicine, then in 1791 began lecturing in chemistry. In 1818 he was awarded a professorship in chemistry and materia medica at <a href=\"/wiki/Glasgow_University\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Glasgow University\">Glasgow University</a>, a role continued until his death.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>As a physician he worked at the Glasgow Royal Mental Hospital, and <a href=\"/wiki/Glasgow_Royal_Infirmary\" title=\"Glasgow Royal Infirmary\">Glasgow Royal Infirmary</a> (previously known as the Old Town Hospital<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>).\n</p><p>He was elected a Fellow of the <a href=\"/wiki/Royal_Society_of_Edinburgh\" title=\"Royal Society of Edinburgh\">Royal Society of Edinburgh</a> in 1790, his proposers being <a href=\"/wiki/Andrew_Dalzell\" title=\"Andrew Dalzell\">Andrew Dalzell</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Dugald_Stewart\" title=\"Dugald Stewart\">Dugald Stewart</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/James_Gregory_(physician)\" title=\"James Gregory (physician)\">James Gregory</a>.\n</p><p>He died in <a href=\"/wiki/Shawfield\" title=\"Shawfield\">Shawfield House</a> near <a href=\"/wiki/Rutherglen\" title=\"Rutherglen\">Rutherglen</a> on 18 June 1821.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>He was originally interred in Blackfriars Churchyard, but the body had to be moved in 1875 when a railway was built through the churchyard. He was reburied in <a href=\"/wiki/Craigton_Cemetery\" title=\"Craigton Cemetery\">Craigton Cemetery</a> with a monument designed by <a href=\"/wiki/Greek_Thomson\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Greek Thomson\">Greek Thomson</a> and sculpted by <a href=\"/wiki/John_Mossman\" title=\"John Mossman\">John Mossman</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> The graves lies near the south-west corner within the second row from the south path.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family\">Family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Robert_Cleghorn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Family\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>He was married to Margaret Thomson (1752\u20131791). They had a daughter, Helen Cleghorn (1790\u20131853)\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Positions_of_note\">Positions of note</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Robert_Cleghorn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Positions of note\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>President of the <a href=\"/wiki/Royal_College_of_Physicians_and_Surgeons_of_Glasgow\" title=\"Royal College of Physicians and Surgeons of Glasgow\">Royal College of Physicians and Surgeons of Glasgow</a> 1788\u20131791</li>\n<li>Honorary president of the <a href=\"/wiki/Royal_Medical_Society\" title=\"Royal Medical Society\">Royal Medical Society</a> in 1781 and full president in 1783.</li>\n<li>Member of the Glasgow Literary Society</li>\n<li>Fellow of the Society of Antiquaries (Scotland)</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Robert_Cleghorn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-gla-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-gla_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://special.lib.gla.ac.uk/manuscripts/search/results_n.cfm?NID=9819&amp;RID=&amp;Y1=&amp;Y2=&amp;M=001\">\"University of Glasgow&#160;:: Manuscripts Catalogue&#160;:: Material relating to Robert Cleghorn\"</a>. <i>special.lib.gla.ac.uk</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">1 July</span> 2018</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=special.lib.gla.ac.uk&amp;rft.atitle=University+of+Glasgow+%3A%3A+Manuscripts+Catalogue+%3A%3A+Material+relating+to+Robert+Cleghorn&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fspecial.lib.gla.ac.uk%2Fmanuscripts%2Fsearch%2Fresults_n.cfm%3FNID%3D9819%26RID%3D%26Y1%3D%26Y2%3D%26M%3D001&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARobert+Cleghorn\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.royalsoced.org.uk/cms/files/fellows/biographical_index/fells_indexp1.pdf\">\"Former Fellows of The Royal Society of Edinburgh 1783 \u2013 2002\"</a> <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(PDF)</span>. Royal Society of Edinburgh. p.&#160;189<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">1 July</span> 2018</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Former+Fellows+of+The+Royal+Society+of+Edinburgh+1783+%E2%80%93+2002&amp;rft.pages=189&amp;rft.pub=Royal+Society+of+Edinburgh&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.royalsoced.org.uk%2Fcms%2Ffiles%2Ffellows%2Fbiographical_index%2Ffells_indexp1.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARobert+Cleghorn\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Physicians and Surgeons in Glasgow, 1599\u20131858, Fiona MacDonald</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">The History of Rutherglen and East Kilbride, David Ure.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.glasgow.gov.uk/CHttpHandler.ashx?id=33048&amp;p=0\">\"Craigton Cemetery Heritage Trail\"</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">1 July</span> 2018</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Craigton+Cemetery+Heritage+Trail&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.glasgow.gov.uk%2FCHttpHandler.ashx%3Fid%3D33048%26p%3D0&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARobert+Cleghorn\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Doctors_stethoscope_2.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d7/Doctors_stethoscope_2.jpg/26px-Doctors_stethoscope_2.jpg\" width=\"26\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia